<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870610-0146 </DOCNO><HL> Advanced Tobacco Assets Sale</HL><DD> 06/10/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> ATPI PHABYTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> SAN ANTONIO, Texas  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Advanced Tobacco Products Inc. said it agreed to sell substantially all its assets to the U.S. unit of Pharmacia AB, Sweden, for $3 million and other considerations.    Advanced Tobacco, which owns a cigarette-substitute product, said it and Pharmacia will develop jointly a quit-smoking product based on Advanced Tobacco's vapor-inhalation technology. Advanced Tobacco will receive additional cash payments over three years, as well as a 3% royalty for at least 10 years following the introduction of any smoking-cessation product developed by the venture.    The transaction is subject to approval by Advanced Tobacco shareholders. </TEXT></DOC>